<a href="/wiki/File:Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Caribou from Wagon Trails.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg/32px-Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg" decoding="async" width="32" height="22" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg/48px-Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg/64px-Caribou_from_Wagon_Trails.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2064" data-file-height="1413" /></a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Animals" title="Portal:Animals">Animals&#32;portal</a></td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%"><div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini"><ul><li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Animal_rights_sidebar" title="Template:Animal rights sidebar"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Animal_rights_sidebar" title="Template talk:Animal rights sidebar"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Animal_rights_sidebar&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>A <b>blood sport</b> or <b>bloodsport</b> is a category of <a href="/wiki/Sport" title="Sport">sport</a> or <a href="/wiki/Entertainment" title="Entertainment">entertainment</a> that involves <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/bloodshed" class="extiw" title="wikt:bloodshed">bloodshed</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-:0_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:0-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Common examples of the former include combat sports such as <a href="/wiki/Cockfight" title="Cockfight">cockfighting</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dog_fighting" title="Dog fighting">dog fighting</a> and some forms of <a href="/wiki/Hunting" title="Hunting">hunting</a> and <a href="/wiki/Fishing" title="Fishing">fishing</a>. Activities characterized as blood sports, but involving only human participants, include the <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Rome" title="Ancient Rome">Ancient Roman</a> <a href="/wiki/Gladiator" title="Gladiator">gladiatorial</a> games.
</p>
